HEADWORD: Acantha
<hw>A*can"tha</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
thorn, fr. <?/ point. See <er>Acute</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A prickle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A spine or prickly fin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The vertebral column; the spinous
process of a vertebra.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acanthaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
